    "• Source code used for building the dataset, training and applying the models, is freely available on AP-HP's GitHub account, distributed under a 3-Clause BSD license.",
    "It is documented, versioned, and citable through Zenodo.",
    "• The results of our experiments will help the community to optimize its annotation process and implementation choices based on our own experience.",
    "Regarding the data and models themselves, access to the CDW's raw data can be granted following the process described on its Web site: eds.aphp.fr.",
    "Prior validation of the access by the local IRB is required."
